<subSubSection id="C315E5E4EF21FFDAFF24A765FDA1FBD0" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB0B66FEF21FFDAFF24A765FDA1FBD0" blockId="1.[151,1436,1045,1613]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis id="B97B6A7DEF21FFDAFF24A765FED1FBAC" bold="true" box="[151,286,1045,1070]" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new genus is named by adding â€“ 
<emphasis id="B97B6A7DEF21FFDAFD7DA765FCC6FBAF" box="[718,777,1045,1069]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="231">oides</emphasis>
posteriorly to its allied genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C0FCDECEF21FFDAFBD7A766FB2AFBAF" box="[1124,1253,1046,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Spazigaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
